  "title" : "Java error when Syncing after Android Studio update from Koala to Narwhal",
  "body" : "<p>My Cordova Android apps** built and ran fine under Android Studio Koala.\nI then updated to Narwhal (2025.1.1).</p>\n<p>Given the deprecation of jcenter(), I followed advice in post &quot;JCenter deprecation; impact on Gradle and Android&quot; and added mavenCentral as a repository.\nSo far so good.</p>\n<p>Studio then complained that the minimum supported Gradle was 8.9.\nSo I updated Gradle to 9.0-milestone-1 and AGP to 8.11.1</p>\n<p>BUT:\nA Sync then immediately gives:</p>\n<p><strong>java.lang.IllegalStateException: No match found</strong>\nwith no further indication of where.</p>\n<p>Upgrading SDK to 36 has not effect.\nI could upgrade Cordova from 7.1.1 to 14.0.1, but I don’t yet want to dig a deeper hole than I am in already!)</p>\n<p>Any suggestions of where to look further (error log ??) to fix the IllegalStateException (above) appreciated</p>\n<p>**  SdkVersion 34; Gradle 7.5; AGP 7.4; Cordova 7.1.1</p>\n"
